Caption: . 🍄 Wrinkled Peach Mushroom 💦 There is no doubt that there are things that I’m missing from the UK. Autumn and Fungi season is definitely one of them. Over the last couple of weeks my good friend Jamie (@this_forest_floor) has been sending me picture, video and even a Skype updates on the patch of red listed, endangered mushies that we shot last year. Like clockwork, exactly a year later, they are emerging in-spite of some of the harshest droughts in London’s history. Im so pleased that Jamie has had the chance to document their growth again this year but it is a shame that I’ve not been able to join in to watch ‘our babies’ (as she called them) grow. Jamie’s love for all things fungi and slime was what started me taking a keen interest into this amazing world. After speaking with Jamie over the last few weeks and watching her spread her fungi love on an interview with @omsystem.cameras yesterday (go watch on YouTube), it has made me pine for all the weird and wonderful fungus that is really lacking where I am in Oz due to it being so dry. I still had a few images from these days out that I’d never released, so it seems like a perfect time to post one now as a little love letter to all things mushroom and as a thank you to the Sloog Queen herself for igniting this passion in me last year, taking me on so many awesome forest walks and showing me many incredible species. Caption: Finalmente aderi ao queridinho das “blogueres de casa” 🤣 O #lysoform Bruto Original (têm outros tipos tbm) é um desinfetante de uso geral, funcionando como: #germicida #bactericida #fungicida. . . . . Esse produto é indicado para uso em limpeza de latas, lixeiras, pias e ralos, uma vez que possui capacidade de eliminar bactérias e germes. Dessa forma a limpeza é feita de forma que o mau cheiro seja eliminado e o ambiente limpo, esse tipo de produto não pode entrar em contato com o corpo humano. . . Ele também pode ser usado na limpeza de ambientes e superfícies laváveis como pisos e azulejos, podendo ser aplicado também nas paredes internas e bordas do vaso sanitário. Outra opção de uso de produto é na limpeza das roupas, usando apenas durante o enxague. . . Quando usado na forma pura o produto age como bactericida, podendo ser usado para desinfetar paredes, armários, maçanetas, entre outras coisas que não são levadas à boca. O indicado é aplicar e deixar agir por dez minutos, outra dica é colocar o produto em uma pequena área do local que deseja aplicar para se certificar de que não irá causar manchas ou danificar o objeto ou local. . . Um alerta do fabricante é que esse produto não pode ser usado por mulheres grávidas 🤰🏻, pois ele possui em sua fórmula o benzeno, substância que pode ocasionar algum tipo de má formação no feto. MODO DE USO: . . Para desodorização diluir um copo (250 Ml) em 10 litros de água. Para lavar roupas use ½ copo (125 Ml) no processo final da lavagem. Não precisa enxaguar. Para desinfecção use o produto puro. Tempo de contato: 10 Minutos. . . Tbm pode ser usado na limpeza de estofado, colchão; para facilitar o uso nesses casos coloque dentro de um borrifador. Date: 2022-02-20 16:14:00
Caption: Happy #SlimeMoldSunday to Myxomycete lovers new and old! These amazing myxo fruiting bodies are Diachea leucopodia, one of my favorites because of their beautiful iridescence.  As with many slime molds, this species changes colors several times during its brief life cycle.  When they first arise from the white plasmodium, the fruiting bodies are white.  They then turn almost black, and as they mature and dry the peridium (outer covering of the spore-containing body) turns into these strikingly beautiful iridescent blue, purple, and brown colors on a white stout stalk.  Although the individual fruiting bodies are tiny, only 1-2mm tall, they can be easy to spot because they grow in dense and large clusters on leaves, grasses, and live and decaying plant material.  To see how tiny they are, see the second photo, which shows a few fruiting bodies on a twig with the tip of a fine point pen for scale. A little technical info for those of you who might be interested.  To photograph such tiny myxos with sharp detail, I use an extreme macro lens.  With such high magnifications, the depth of field (portion of the subject that is in sharp focus) is less than 0.05mm. To get a photo of the entire fruiting body in focus, I use a technique called focus stacking. My camera is mounted on a finely tuned rail, and the camera is moved in minuscule increments between each photo, so that the focal point changes with each photo.   For this photo, I took 138 individual images, which were then “stacked” with specialized computer software that combines the most in-focus portions of each of the individual images into a composite image that shows everything in focus from front to back.

Caption: Here are various stages of growth of Mycena manipularis (syn.=Filoboletus/Favolaschia manipularis) aka “Luminous Porecaps”. While these are bioluminescent - I show what they look like in daylight. Note: the second image has a different species in the mix, as Luminous Porecaps (as the name suggests-have pores, not gills). Date: 2020-11-26 03:59:14
Caption: Níscalo – Robellón – Callampa rosada . El género Lactarius comprende casi 600 especies ectomicorrícicas pertenecientes a la familia Russulaceae. Su mayor característica es la segregación de un látex de color que varía según la especie y que tiene apariencia lechosa, cualidad que le da el epíteto a su género, pues Lactarius proviene del latín “lac” que significa “leche”, siendo el ejemplar probablemente más conocido Lactarius deliciosus. . Esta especie se encuentra en plantaciones forestales de Pinus radiata en Chile y su aparición es otoñal e invernal, aunque en ciertas condiciones puede extender incluso hasta verano. Es una seta muy fácil de identificar, a grandes rasgos: tiene una forma de embudo, es quebradizo, con sombrero de color crema a anaranjado, convexo que se aplana con la edad, sobre la superficie del píleo tiene círculos concéntricos; las láminas son adnadas y decurrentes, de color naranjo vivo o zanahoria, al rasgarlas exuda el látex y este se oxida con la presencia de aire dejando un color verdoso; y el pie es cilíndrico, concolor al sombrero, macizo al inicio y luego hueco. . Se trata de una especie muy distintiva por estas características, sin embargo hay otra especie muy parecida en el país: L. quieticolor, que correspondería a la imagen, pues tiene un sombrero mucho más pálido y blanquecino a diferencia de L. deliciosus que tiene el sombrero más anaranjado fuerte y que en apreciación del profesor Gotz es la especie que estaría mayormente en Chile en las plantaciones de pino insigne. . . Lactarius quieticolor Romagn. . . #nature #mushroom #fungi #hongos #seta #fungiworld #mushroomspotting #mycology #fungilove #fungifun #funghi #woods #forest #mycophile #fungus #mushroomlover #fungifreaks #micelium #fantasticfungi #mushroomlove #mushroomhunting #fungo #fungiphotography #mushroomsociety #hongosdechile #lactarius #milkcap

Caption: No son plantas, tampoco animales, entonces... ¿Qué son? 🤔🍄 Las setas o callampas que solemos ver en otoño, de diversas formas, tamaños y colores son la parte exterior de algunos hongos que viven bajo tierra o dentro de la materia orgánica en descomposición 🦠🍄 Los hongos son uno de los cinco reinos en que se agrupan a los seres vivos y, por lo tanto, no se consideran ni plantas, ni animales 🍄 No son vegetales, pues no realizan fotosíntesis. Tampoco son animales, pues no ingieren su alimento, lo absorben y sus células tienen pared celular 🧬🍄 Debido a estas razones estos organismos están situados en su propio reino biológico llamado Fungi 🍄 Está es solo una de las muchas curiosidades que podemos aprender sobre estos importantes y lindos seres vivos 🥹🍄 Aprovecho que es otoño temporada donde los vemos por todas partes, así iré enseñando fotitos y videos de las variedades que encontré por estos lados, y por supuesto otras curiosidades sobre ellos 🍄🍄 Recuerda darle amor a este post 💚 #hongo #otoño #hongos #fungi #vidafungi #fungilove #naturaleza #plantas #lamacetitachile #fungichile #valdivia #amanita #amanitas

Caption: It’s always a delight to find a pop of color in the woods during the winter months. 🧡 The fruiting bodies of the mock oyster are a lovely sherbet orange with fuzzy caps and crowded gills. They drop a very pale pink spore print, so be sure when conducting a print to use white paper. Most people say they stink, but I’ve never experienced that when finding these. They can be found growing in clustered rows on dead hardwood trees, but can also be found on conifers. 🆔: Phyllotopsis nidulans | mock oyster . . . #mycology #mycologymonday #foragervibes #mockoyster #wintermushrooms #phyllotopsis #phyllotopsisnidulans #nidulariaceae #fungikingdom #fungihunting #fungiphoto #fungiofinstagram #fantasticfungi #planetfungi #mushrooms_of_our_world #oklahomamushrooms

Date: 2022-08-02 05:09:43
Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Date: 2023-12-26 08:09:47
Caption: "Magic Mushroom Cultivation” by Steven Pollock M.D. (1977) is one of the legendary texts in the cultivation of "magic mushrooms". Many popular books were published in the US during the 70’s about the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., but this one stands out as one of the better known, particularly because in time Pollock was (incorrectly) associated with the cubensis strain "P envy". Pollock is also well known for finding and cultivating P. tampanensis, aka "Philosophers Stones". Psilocybe cubensis is one of the most cultivated mushrooms, and as a consequence of extensive collection, cultivation, breeding, and marketing ploys by various spore print sellers numerous “strains” now exist. Unfortunately, much of the history of many of the older strains has been lost, or exist within obfuscated narratives from a variety of websites, with the person/s responsible having disappeared into history. Cailleux and Heim were the first to grow cultures of P. cubensis (as Stropharia cubensis), publishing their methods in 1957. During the late 1960’s and early 1970’s, those with access to scientific literature adapted laboratory techniques for the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., notably R.E. Brown and associates who published “The Psychedelic Guide to the Preparation of the Eucharist in a Few of Its Many Guises” which was the first countercultural text to mention the cultivation of P. cubensis. Other books include “Growing Wild Mushrooms” by Harris (1976), “Psilocybin: Magic Mushroom Grower's Guide” by Oss & Oeric (1976), “How to Identify and Grow Psilocybin Mushrooms” by Gutierrez & Stevens (1977), “Teonanácatl : hallucinogenic mushrooms of North America” by Ott & Bigwood (1978), and “The mushroom Cultivator” by Stamets and Chilton(1983) #guerrillamycology #🍄 #thinkfungi #fungi #funghi #fungus #hongos #mushrooms #mycology #mycophile #mycophilia #fungiculture  #fungifanatic #mycelium #myceliumrunning #ethnomycology #radicalmycology #hallucinogenicfungi #hallucinogenic #entheogens #rogerheim #pollock #stevenpollock #magicmushroomcultivation #psilocybe #psilocybecubensis #psychedelicliterautre #penvy #philosophersstones #mushroomcultivation

Caption: AUSTROPAXILUS SP. - Graciela Vicente de @recetasysetas nos comparte este ser fascinante, acompañado de una ficha para ayudarnos en la identificación de esta especie. Este ejemplar podría tratarse de Austropaxilus statuum, aunque sin estudios adicionales, no podemos asegurar la especie con certeza. Características: 📸 Ubicación: Chile ⚠️🍽️ Tóxico 🍁 Estación: Otoño 🌿 Hábitat: Bosque nativo 📏 Tamaño: Hongo de tamaño medio, de unos 10-12 cm. Forma: Similar a una copa con el sombrero algo deprimido en la parte central. Color: Cutícula suave de color amarillo dorado con descamaciones más oscuras. Láminas: Muy decurrentes, de color amarillo. Pie: Corto y amarillo. Corte: Su carne enrojece al cortarla. Textura: Fibroso, de olor fenólico y sabor amargo. Esporada: Parda-amarillenta. Confusiones Posibles: Paxilus involutus - Asociado a álamos. Cantharellus cibarius - Comestible europeo que no se encuentra en Chile. 🍴 Comestibilidad: Este hongo es tóxico y provoca graves daños gastrointestinales, por lo que se desaconseja su consumo. Caption: Amanita muscaria🍄 es una especie cosmopolita que crece en el sur de Chile🇨🇱, principalmente en la zona de Valdivia y sus alrededores, sin embargo se puede encontrar en casi todas las zonas donde existen predios forestales plantados con pino🌲 radiata. El único uso documentado para Amanita muscaria corresponde a la utilización en contexto chamanico. Aunque Amanita muscaria es un hongo cosmopolita solo ha sido utilizado en algunas culturas indígenas de Estados Unidos🇺🇸, Rusia 🇷🇺y Mesoamérica. Actualmente, Amanita muscaria es consumido a baja escala como un alucinógeno 😵‍💫de uso recreativo, en donde no existe un guía o Chaman. Por lo cual resulta en la mayoría de las ocasiones un consumo irresponsable y bastante peligroso. No existe ningún proceso seguro que elimine todas las toxinas en A. muscaria, sin embargo, si se va a consumir se recomienda secarla al sol, pues este proceso disminuye la toxicidad de la muscarina o toxina mata moscas. El secado al sol🌞 también ayuda en la descarboxilación parcial del ácido iboténico, el cual se transforma en muscimol, sustancia que es aproximadamente 10 veces más alucinógeno. La acción farmacológica del muscimol es diferente de la psilocibina (Psilocibes spp. “Cucumelo”), ya que actúa como agonista del receptor GABAa. Los riesgos pueden disminuir más si se consume solo la película roja externa del sombrero y la capa que yace inmediatamente por debajo, en el hongo seco. 🛑NUNCA SE DEBE CONSUMIR FRESCO y siempre acompañado de un cuidador o alguna persona que no consuma. 👉Ante todas las recomendaciones pertinentes, siempre es mejor no consumir Amanita muscaria para su uso recreativo. 🛩️Comparte si te gustó Créditos @mushroom_and_us @vicentevaldesguzmanphotography #amanita #amanitamuscaria #setas #hongos #fungi #reinofungi #fungilover #picfee #fotoverweij #photographersassociates #ig_discover_holland #igholland #dutch_connextion #catch_holland #dutchphotoacademy #thiswaymoments #heelnederland_fotografeert #holland_photolovers #nb_nature_brilliance #vroegevogels_bnnvara

Date: 2020-11-26 03:59:14
Caption: Níscalo – Robellón – Callampa rosada . El género Lactarius comprende casi 600 especies ectomicorrícicas pertenecientes a la familia Russulaceae. Su mayor característica es la segregación de un látex de color que varía según la especie y que tiene apariencia lechosa, cualidad que le da el epíteto a su género, pues Lactarius proviene del latín “lac” que significa “leche”, siendo el ejemplar probablemente más conocido Lactarius deliciosus. . Esta especie se encuentra en plantaciones forestales de Pinus radiata en Chile y su aparición es otoñal e invernal, aunque en ciertas condiciones puede extender incluso hasta verano. Es una seta muy fácil de identificar, a grandes rasgos: tiene una forma de embudo, es quebradizo, con sombrero de color crema a anaranjado, convexo que se aplana con la edad, sobre la superficie del píleo tiene círculos concéntricos; las láminas son adnadas y decurrentes, de color naranjo vivo o zanahoria, al rasgarlas exuda el látex y este se oxida con la presencia de aire dejando un color verdoso; y el pie es cilíndrico, concolor al sombrero, macizo al inicio y luego hueco. . Se trata de una especie muy distintiva por estas características, sin embargo hay otra especie muy parecida en el país: L. quieticolor, que correspondería a la imagen, pues tiene un sombrero mucho más pálido y blanquecino a diferencia de L. deliciosus que tiene el sombrero más anaranjado fuerte y que en apreciación del profesor Gotz es la especie que estaría mayormente en Chile en las plantaciones de pino insigne. . . Lactarius quieticolor Romagn. . . #nature #mushroom #fungi #hongos #seta #fungiworld #mushroomspotting #mycology #fungilove #fungifun #funghi #woods #forest #mycophile #fungus #mushroomlover #fungifreaks #micelium #fantasticfungi #mushroomlove #mushroomhunting #fungo #fungiphotography #mushroomsociety #hongosdechile #lactarius #milkcap

Date: 2021-02-01 00:45:31
Caption: You might have read our recent post about the excessive use of damaging pesticides in imported cut flowers, but of almost equal concern is fungicide usage. You see, Ecuador, where many of the roses sold in the US are grown, has high amounts of rainfall and the greenhouses where these flowers are grown are notorious for holding in humidity and creating fungus issues like Botrytis. Botrytis can create spots on a rose, and often won't appear on a rose until after it's left the farm. To prevent these spots from showing up on roses once they hit the retail market and dissuading customers from buying them, foreign growers have developed a worrisome and toxic method of dipping the entire rose into a vat of fungicide, first dunking the bloom, and then the stem. The workers in charge of this job wear respirator masks to avoid inhaling the products, which are then packaged directly into flower sleeves and shipped to the US (no, they are not rinsed off afterward). Of the 37 products that are used as rose dip treatments, 17 of them have been identified by the Pesticide Action Network to be problematic as groundwater pollutants or harmful to humans, toxic to life and the environment. Unfortunately, Valentine's Day, the biggest flower holiday in the US, is also a time when domestic roses are, by and large, dormant in their fields. This means the VAST majority of cut roses purchased during February have been dipped in a toxic blend of fungicides and pesticides. Not exactly the way I'd want to say "I love you!" #flowers #colorado #coloradoflorist #farmerflorist #coloradofarmer #localflowers #pesticides #fungicides #toxicflowers #valentinesdayflowers #valentinesday #denver #denverflorist #roses #importedroses #buyamericangrown #americangrown #supportlocalflowers #supportamericanfarms #buyamericangrown #coloradogrown #freshcutcolorado #coloradoflowers

Date: 2024-06-01 06:25:45
Caption: 🍄 🥰 🍄 🐛 🍄 🐌 🍄 🆔 𝘌𝘯𝘵𝘰𝘭𝘰𝘮𝘢 𝘸𝘢𝘪𝘬𝘢𝘳𝘦𝘮𝘰𝘢𝘯𝘢 🌐 Arnold Dam, Moana, New Zealand ⏰ 1st June 2024 Definitely my favorite first find of 2023/2024 fungi season. From this post onwards, I will also try to take a video clip to show the surrounding of the mushroom and possibly let you have the idea of the actual size of the mushroom featured in my individual post. -------------------------------------------- 𝗣𝗵𝗼𝘁𝗼 𝟭 📷 𝗢𝗹𝘆𝗺𝗽𝘂𝘀 𝗢𝗠𝗗 𝗘𝗠𝟭 𝗠𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗜𝗜𝗜 🔭 𝗭𝘂𝗶𝗸𝗼 𝟲𝟬𝗺𝗺 𝗠𝗮𝗰𝗿𝗼 𝗟𝗲𝗻𝘀 ⚙️ 𝟭/𝟭𝟬 𝘀𝗲𝗰, 𝗙𝟮.𝟴 📚 𝟯𝟬 𝗽𝗵𝗼𝘁𝗼𝘀 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗱 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗛𝗲𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗼𝗻 𝗙𝗼𝗰𝘂𝘀 𝗣𝗿𝗼 𝗣𝗵𝗼𝘁𝗼 𝟮 📷 𝗢𝗹𝘆𝗺𝗽𝘂𝘀 𝗢𝗠𝗗 𝗘𝗠𝟭 𝗠𝗮𝗿𝗸𝗜𝗜𝗜 🔭 𝗭𝘂𝗶𝗸𝗼 𝟲𝟬𝗺𝗺 𝗠𝗮𝗰𝗿𝗼 𝗟𝗲𝗻𝘀 ⚙️ 𝟭/𝟱 𝘀𝗲𝗰, 𝗙𝟮.𝟴 📚 𝟱𝟬 𝗽𝗵𝗼𝘁𝗼𝘀 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗰𝗸𝗲𝗱 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵 𝗛𝗲𝗹𝗶𝗰𝗼𝗻 𝗙𝗼𝗰𝘂𝘀 𝗣𝗿𝗼 -------------------------------------------- #entolomahochstetteri #blue #mushroomofinstagram #mushroomsofnewzealand #fantasticfungi #fungi #fungiofinstagram #macrofungi #nature #mushroomphotography @omsystem.cameras #champignons #svampe #pilze #kinoko #cendawan #hongos #beoseos #버섯 #funghi #earthday #paddestoel #champiñón #sieni #sveppir #arnolddam #westcoastnz #focusstacking #fungling

Caption: ℹ️ Dünnsporiges Kranzbecherchen (Vibrissea flavorirens) Vibrissea flavorirens ist ein Bewohner sauberer Bäche, Quellsümpfe usw. Es besiedelt, oft sehr zahlreich, entrindete, harte Laubholzäste, die ständig von fließendem Wasser umspült werden. Die Apothecien werden ca 2-3mm groß, sind kurz gestielt und haben einen charakteristischen, zahnradähnlich gekerbten Rand. Die dünnen Fäden, die auf dem letzten Bild im Hintergrund herumfliegen, sind die, mit bis 250μm Länge, riesigen Sporen. 🗓️ 26.05.2024 🍴 ungenießbar 🚩 Rote Liste (DE): Vorwarnliste #vibrisseaflavovirens #dünnsporigeskranzbecherchen #pilze #fungi #mushrooms #mycology #nature #pilzfotografie #mushroomphotography #pilzesammeln #pilzesuchen #mushroomhunting #mushroomsofınstagram #fungiofinstagram #fungilove #fantasticfungi #fungifreaks #makrofotografie #macrophotography #forestfinds #darmstadt #spessart #rotelistepilze

Cuando voy al bosque suelo sentarme a observar ,así puedo ver bien a mi alrededor, no tengo la certeza con lo que me voy a encontrar aunque el bosque siempre me sorprende, me incita a seguir explorando este fascinante y poco conocido mundo, como este honguito, que a mi me encanta por su color,textura y sus lamelas. Su hábitat se encuentra entre el humus húmedo en tocones de madera (descomposicion) y sobre la corteza de arboles vivos dentro del bosque. Se caracteriza por su látex rojo al dañarse o romperse. Su sombrero es de color rojo o rosado en la juventud , tornándose rojo marrón al madurar ,su contextura es frágil y delicada ,como gran parte del género de las denominadas mycenas. . . . . . . . #instagood #instatravel #instagram #instafungi #instagram #naturephotography #naturelovers #naturegram #funga #fungiphotography #fungi #fungifanatic #fungi_fan_club #fantasticfungi #mushrooms #chile_shots #chilegram #chilenunaimagen #chile #chileannature #chile🇨🇱 #funga #macro #macrophotography #macro_perfection #macronature #lugaresbonitosdechile #chilenosamantesdelanaturaleza #mostremoschile #instagood #instaphoto

Date: 2023-11-10 16:00:59
Caption: The brightly-coloured waxcaps are often thought of as the orchids of the fungi kingdom because they are so vibrant and showy, and also quite particular. They will only grow on undisturbed, nutrient-poor grasslands like ancient pasture and other land that has never been ploughed or fertilised. As a result, many species are rare and hard to find but some grow much closer to home – literally. Waxcaps can appear in garden lawns, grassy churchyards and even the occasional cricket pitch as long as the conditions are right. Wherever you find them, their presence means you’re in a very special place. Scarlet Waxcap © Graeme Lyons This image features in our 2024 Wildlife of Sussex Calendar, available from our online shop - see link in bio #Sussex #Waxcap #FungiFriday

Caption: #SanValentino è sinonimo di baci, cioccolatini ma soprattutto… #fiori! Immancabili le #rose, simbolo di #passione per eccellenza. Ma vale la pena fare regalarle alla persona amata? La risposta – nella maggior parte dei casi – è no. O almeno se si vuole fare un bel regalo all’#ambiente. In vista di questa celebrazione, infatti, tonnellate di rose refrigerate vengono trasportate da Paesi del Sud America e dell’Africa orientale all’Europa, dove vengono poi vendute spesso a caro prezzo. Ma dietro la bellezza di questi fiori si nascondono veri e propri cocktail di #pesticidi, comprese quelle certificate Fairtrade. A svelare il lato oscuro delle rose è la recente analisi condotta dalla rivista tedesca Öko-Test. In totale sono stati 21 i #mazzidirose esaminati, venduti da note aziende leader nella consegna dei fiori come Fleurop e Euroflorist. E il numero di diversi pesticidi rilevati è impressionante: ben 54. Oltre 3/4 dei boquet hanno riportato dei punteggi scarsi o insufficienti, inclusi quelli molto costosi. I prezzi sono molto variabili: vanno da 1,99 euro per dodici rose a 39,95 euro per otto rose. Fra le sostanze rilevate vi sono anche fitofarmaci potenzialmente cancerogeni, mutageni, reprotossici e tossici per le api. Ma non finisce qua. Su 3/4 dei mezzi di fiori analizzati è stato spruzzato uno spray a base di #insetticida Thiacloprid e di #fungicida Carbendazim, messi al bando in Europa. Secondo l’Agenzia europea per le sostanze chimiche (ECHA), questa sostanze sono potenzialmente cangerogene e possono influenzare la fertilità e provocare danni nei nascituri. Quando si parla di rose, c’è un altro fattore da considerare oltre alla spinosa questione dei pesticidi: ovvero lo #sfruttamentodeilavoratori. Nella maggior parte dei casi le rose arrivano da Paesi africani come il Kenya, fino al 70% di quelli presenti sul mercato europeo. Qui migliaia di lavoratori sono costretti a turni pesanti per paghe da fame e le donne, in molti casi, sono vittime di molestie sessuali. Gran parte delle rose vendute negli Usa e in Europa arriva anche dalla Colombia e dall’Ecuador, Paesi in cui lo sfruttamento minorile è molto radicato. . . #greenme #greenmeitalia

Caption: Fungicida natural e eficaz para tomates 🍅 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Hoje partilho uma receita de fungicida natural simples de preparar em casa e que pode ser útil para prevenir ou tratar as doenças fúngicas mais comuns desta planta, como é o caso do oídio e míldio. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝗮 𝗽𝗿𝗲𝘃𝗲𝗻𝗰̧𝗮̃𝗼: ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Preparação: Fazer regas com leite diluído: 3 copos de leite para 7 copos de água. Aplicação: Deve ser aplicado de manhã, regando uma a duas vezes por semana. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ 𝗣𝗮𝗿𝗮 𝘁𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗮𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁𝗼: ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ Preparação: Diluir 1 copo de leite em 4 copos de água. Agitar a mistura e pulverizar. Aplicação: Aplicar duas vezes por semana se as folhas já estiverem com sintomas evidentes de oídio. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ❗️Não esqueçam que o ideal será realizar as pulverizações, preferencialmente de forma preventiva, quando as condições climáticas forem favoráveis ao aparecimento de doenças. Após o seu estabelecimento, a maioria das doenças é complicada de controlar ou pode nem ser controlada. . . . #cultivosdacaseiro #tomate #fungicida #fungicidanatural #receitasdahora #plantasdahorta #hortaurbana #hortas #plantar #plantarnavaranda #tomates #tratamentosnaturais #doencasdahorticultura #agricultura #agriculturaurbana #selvaurbana #tomateiro #primavera #plantlover #tomatoes #gardens #growyourownfood #instagardeners #slowliving #urbanjungle

Caption: Fomitopsis betulina EN This species is a saprotroph or parasite specific to Betula spp. It can be found on logs, dead trees, but sometimes in live trees too, although it possibly only infects already decaying, trees. Like other brown rot fungi it degrades the carbohydrate fraction of lignocellulose but, in contrast to white rot fungi, leaves lignin in the form of cubical brown fragments. In Portugal I have only found them growing in high altitude in mountainous areas. PT Esta espécie é um saprófito ou parasita específico de espécies do género Betula. Pode observar-se em troncos e ramos, árvores mortas, mas por vezes também em espécimes vivos, provavelmente aproveitando árvores já em mau estado fitossanitário em que a infeção é mais fácil de propagar. Como outros fungos de podridão castanha degrada a parte dos hidratos de carbono(celulose) da lignocelulose, deixando a lignina na forma de fragmentos cúbicos castanhos, em contraste com os fungos de podridão branca que degradam na forma oposta. Em Portugal só encontrei esta espécie em habitats de altitude em serras. Even with harsh weather changes like these, there is one #supercrop that can grow year-round in a controlled indoor environment, and still be incredibly #sustainable 🌱 @ilfungoeclettico 👀‼️ Considering the drastic changes of temperature in one day, we wanted to satisfy both warm and cold cravings ✨ For the zuppa di giorno, @pinasiotto went with a twist on the iconic #Pancotto but with fungi, chives, asparagi, and a generous sprinkle of Parmigiano 💛 I took the lead with a Fungiche, a #plantbased twist on a #PeruvianCeviche 🇵🇪 Slow-cooked #Pleurotus Florida marinated in tomato water, red onion, lemon and orange juice 🍊 For a sweet and smoky taste, we added charred bell peppers, and finished with a celery, ginger, and cilantro “leche de tigre” 🐯 🧆 As a bonus, of course I got to try their Lentil Falafel with a cucumber pico de gallo and smoked eggplant sauce Once again, I am so thankful for this empowering hub that continues to encourage me to let go of fears and just have fun(gi) 🤣💜 @cristina_fiorese #pastonomade #pastonomadebologna #ilfungoeclettico #urbanmushrooms #urbanfungi #fungigrowing #fungifreaks #vegetariancooking #vegetariancuisine #veganceviche #cevichevegano #cevichevegetariano #fungiculture #fungicultura #pleurotusflorida

Date: 2022-10-03 11:47:28
Caption: Dendrocollybia racemosa - Branched shanklet Not my find but a collaborative effort to collect and record this rare species. I’m thrilled to get the opportunity to witness this one. The location has been recorded, and pending permissions, a sample will be making its way to Kew Gardens to be included in their genome sequencing projects and the national collection. Found by: Nicky Freeman Collected & record by: Iona Fraser @ashdownforage The species is characterised by its unusual stem, which is covered with short lateral branches. The branches often produce spherical slimeheads of translucent conidiophores  on their swollen tips. The conidiophores produce conidia (asexual spores) by mitosis. Because the fungus can rely on either sexual or asexual modes of reproduction, fruit bodies sometimes have reduced or even missing caps. The unusual stems originate from black pea-sized structures called sclerotia. The anamorphic form of the fungus, known as Tilachlidiopsis racemosa, is missing the sexual stage of its life cycle. It can reproduce at relatively low temperatures, an adaptation believed to improve its ability to grow quickly and fruit on decomposing mushrooms. (Info via Wikimili) #allthingsfungi

Caption: No son plantas, tampoco animales, entonces... ¿Qué son? 🤔🍄 Las setas o callampas que solemos ver en otoño, de diversas formas, tamaños y colores son la parte exterior de algunos hongos que viven bajo tierra o dentro de la materia orgánica en descomposición 🦠🍄 Los hongos son uno de los cinco reinos en que se agrupan a los seres vivos y, por lo tanto, no se consideran ni plantas, ni animales 🍄 No son vegetales, pues no realizan fotosíntesis. Tampoco son animales, pues no ingieren su alimento, lo absorben y sus células tienen pared celular 🧬🍄 Debido a estas razones estos organismos están situados en su propio reino biológico llamado Fungi 🍄 Está es solo una de las muchas curiosidades que podemos aprender sobre estos importantes y lindos seres vivos 🥹🍄 Aprovecho que es otoño temporada donde los vemos por todas partes, así iré enseñando fotitos y videos de las variedades que encontré por estos lados, y por supuesto otras curiosidades sobre ellos 🍄🍄 Recuerda darle amor a este post 💚 #hongo #otoño #hongos #fungi #vidafungi #fungilove #naturaleza #plantas #lamacetitachile #fungichile #valdivia #amanita #amanitas

Caption: Gallacea Scleroderma is one of New Zealand’s varieties of pouch fungi with fleshy, enclosed fruiting bodies. Truffles are ascomycete fungi, but most of these New Zealand pouch fungi are basidiomycetes. The gills are packed tight inside the pouch and they sit in many different genera. . Their spores are thought to be often spread by birds. They are very cool fungi. #fungus #fungi #mycology #fungihunting #newzealandfungi #newzealand #fungiphotography #macrophotography

Date: 2022-08-02 05:09:43
Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Caption: Hexagonia tenuis fungi is plentiful in the regenerating native forests at the base of the escarpment. These areas were originally cleared for farmland and mining. The returning forests are only approximately 50 years into the process of establishing themselves again and I'm always in awe of their regenerative power. It's hard not to amorphosize natural phenomena with the constraints our language puts upon us. Fungi networks are described like the internet, beehives are described like officeworkers, but we know this is a crude way to narrate the complexity, abstraction, mystery and full expression of nature. So I tread tentatively knowing these words that follow are inept, but to experience a regenerating forest is to be part of a continual homecoming. With each species of native flora and fauna that returns I personally am exalted but there is no fanfare, fireworks or roll call within the forest itself. Instead a palatable gathering of strength and an emerging tranquillity spreads as each species reestablishes itself within the dynamics of the forest family. Many of the photos in this gallery are from this regenerating forest and it is a joy to share the homecoming of species like this fungi with you. #mycology #mycologysociety #fungus #mycologyphotography #fungilover #fungiphotography #fungifanatic #fantasticfungi #fungiofinstagram #fungiownunder #fungihunter #fungiaustralia #fungifreaks #fungihunting #fungiidentification #fungikingdom #fungilove #fungiphotography #fungioftheday #mushroom #mushrooms #mushlove #mushroomphotography #mushroomsofinstagram #australianfungi #fungi #forestbathing #forestfinds #naturesbeauty #forestlovers #biodiversity

Caption: These miniature white mushrooms are part of a large genus of small saprotrophic mushrooms called Mycena that are rarely more than a few centimeters in width. They are characterized by a white spore print, a small conical or bell-shaped cap, and a thin fragile stem. Date: 2022-03-22 20:18:52
Caption: 💙 Happy World Water Day! 🌊 Without water, there is no us and no mushrooms. Our town Tzununa, is named after the indiginous name of the lake. Tzunu = hummingbird, na=water. Water is also a challenge here, all of our waters are invested with parasites like E.Coli, Giardia and many more unwanted visitors. We are blessed enough to be able to properly filter our water, not all of our local neighbors have this ability. It is in this spirit that we, feel so passionate about water quality in our home of Lake Atitlan, Guatemala. We have since partnered with a local NGO, ​@water4lifeglobal ​ Water 4 Life Global is working to provide families in Guatemala access to clean water. Their clean water initiatives include the distribution of water filter technology, collaboration on biological water treatment plans and contributions towards the reforestation of Lake Atitlán. ​ The greater vision of Water 4 Life Global is nothing less than the availability of clean drinking water that is easily accessible and sustained for many years. Their team envisions a life free of water transmitted diseases, water toxins, malnutrition, and environmental damage, in a country that maintains each of these issues as very viable threats to the communities and ecosystems. As a monthly donor, we proudly stand by the work of Water 4 Life Global. When you enroll in our Sacred Mushroom Cultivation Course, you too are supporting indigenous families and the waterways of Tzununa, Guatemala. Tap the link in our @fungiacademy bio to learn about growing your own mushrooms while supporting this cause 💧🍄 Photo repost from @ecoerotica (Photo credit unknown. Please tag if you know!) . . . #alteredstates #energyhealing #worldwaterday #waterpollution #ecowarriors #protecttheearth #saveourplanet #savetheearth #worldwaterday💦 #worldwaterday💧 #fungifacts #mycologyjunkie #mycologycommunity #mushroomtherapy #mushroomgrowers #mushaf #mycologylife #artofthemushroom #mycophile #mushroomart #fungi #naturesmedicine

Date: 2024-06-03 13:03:14
Caption: 🆔Inosperma erubescens (Inocybe erubescens) 👉🏽Deadly Fibrecap, brick-red tear mushroom 👉🏽Ziegelroter Risspilz 👉🏽变红丝盖伞 (reddening silk top umbrella) 🌟 The brick-red splitting mushroom (Inocybe erubescens) can be found on forest paths, in parks, or in deciduous forests, especially under beech or linden trees on calcareous, nutrient-rich soils. 🌳🍃 The fruit bodies of this mushroom appear from spring/early summer until late autumn. 🌸🍂 🌟 磚紅裂褶菇（Inocybe erubescens）可以在林間小徑、公園或闊葉林中找到，特別是在含鈣、富營養的土壤中的山毛櫸或菩提樹下。🌳🍃 這種蘑菇的子實體從春季/初夏到晚秋出現。🌸🍂 ⚠️ **WARNING:** Inocybe erubescens contains a potentially fatal dose of the toxin muscarine. ⚠️😱 However, its deadly toxicity depends on the amount consumed; a small piece might not cause severe illness, but eating an entire mushroom can be fatal. 🍄☠️ ⚠️ **警告：** 磚紅裂褶菇含有致命劑量的毒素——毒蕈鹼。⚠️😱 然而，其致命毒性取決於攝入量；少量可能不會引起嚴重疾病，但食用整個蘑菇可能致命。🍄☠️ 📚 All mushroom guidebooks and mushroom hunters advise against consuming any members of the Inocybaceae family! ❌🚫 📚 所有的蘑菇指南書和蘑菇獵人都建議不要食用任何Inocybaceae科的成員！❌🚫 Today, when I discovered these Inocybe mushrooms in the village next to some linden trees, I had to lie down on the ground to take pictures and examine them carefully. 📸👀 This was when a car stopped right behind me, and a man got out to ask if everything was okay. 🚗💨 I felt a bit awkward but reassured him that I was fine. 😅 It was heartening to see that people care if someone is spread out on the ground, regardless of the reason. ❤️🙏 今天，當我在村子裡的一些菩提樹旁發現這些裂褶菇時，我不得不躺在地上拍照並仔細檢查它們。📸👀 就在這時，一輛車停在我身後，一位男士下車問我是否一切正常。🚗💨 我感到有點尷尬，但我向他保證我沒事。😅 看到人們關心無論何種原因躺在地上的人，這讓我感到很暖心。❤️🙏 #InocybeErubescens 🍄🌿🕵️‍♂️ I tried some microscopy on this one. 🔬🧬 Image one shows cheilocystidia, and in between the two big cheilocystidia is a basidium with two sterigmata (they look like tiny antennas). 🧫🔍 The second microscopy image shows spores, which are oval to almond-shaped. I used Melzer's reagent to stain the sample. 🧪📸 Oh my, microscopy terminology is really hard! Definitely need to catch up. 😅 In case you know any of the terms in Chinese, please feel free to comment. Cheilozystidia 緣擔孢子囊 Basidia 擔子 Sterigmata 擔梗

Date: 2024-05-30 23:23:35
Caption: AUSTROPAXILUS SP. - Graciela Vicente de @recetasysetas nos comparte este ser fascinante, acompañado de una ficha para ayudarnos en la identificación de esta especie. Este ejemplar podría tratarse de Austropaxilus statuum, aunque sin estudios adicionales, no podemos asegurar la especie con certeza. Características: 📸 Ubicación: Chile ⚠️🍽️ Tóxico 🍁 Estación: Otoño 🌿 Hábitat: Bosque nativo 📏 Tamaño: Hongo de tamaño medio, de unos 10-12 cm. Forma: Similar a una copa con el sombrero algo deprimido en la parte central. Color: Cutícula suave de color amarillo dorado con descamaciones más oscuras. Láminas: Muy decurrentes, de color amarillo. Pie: Corto y amarillo. Corte: Su carne enrojece al cortarla. Textura: Fibroso, de olor fenólico y sabor amargo. Esporada: Parda-amarillenta. Confusiones Posibles: Paxilus involutus - Asociado a álamos. Cantharellus cibarius - Comestible europeo que no se encuentra en Chile. 🍴 Comestibilidad: Este hongo es tóxico y provoca graves daños gastrointestinales, por lo que se desaconseja su consumo. Descubre más sobre la diversidad fúngica en nuestra región y aprende a identificar las especies y las mejores recetas fungi con Graciela Vicente. ¡Sigamos explorando el fascinante mundo de los hongos! #reinofungi #setas #hongo #mushroom #nativo #fungi ¿Ya te encontraste con esta especie? Cuéntanos en comentarios sobre qué otros hongos te gustaría saber más.

Caption: The #Zellers_bolete also known as #Xerocomellus_zelleri) is a solitary mushroom characterised by blackish cap that  appears to shimmer pearlescent under right light. This mushroom's underside is comprised of tightly spaced pores of golden yellow that fade to putrid green with age. It appeara in #coniferous #forests, and also on hardwoods. Its best frature is that It forms symbiotic relationships with tree roots to exchange vital nutrients with its hosts. Fruitbodies will be found popping up from the soil beneath a host tree. However, this is not the case with all its hosts, when it appears beneath redwoods, these trees are not very keen to engage in these symbiotic relationship. . . . . . . #fungi #fungilover #mushrooms #fungiporn #fantasticfungi #mycologicalsociety #mycologyaustralia #mycologicalsocietyofuk #foraging #autumn #mycelium #shrooms #fungi_fan_club #fungiidentification #fungihunter #fungiphotos #fungistan #nationalgeographic #naturephotography #nature #naturelovers #reinofungi #hongos🍄 #fungus #fungusphotography

Labels:

Date: 2024-05-31 21:30:36
Caption: ✨𝗜𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝘆𝘅’✨ Imaginez un organisme à la croisée des règnes animal et végétal, qui se développe comme une plante mais se déplace comme un animal. C’est 𝗖𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗺𝘆𝘅𝗮 𝗳𝗿𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗮, un myxomycète. Il se présente sous une forme étonnante, rappelant un corail miniature ou de minuscules stalactites. Ses ramifications blanches se développent sur les bois morts, formant des structures délicates et complexes. Ces ramifications, mesurant jusqu’à 4 millimètres de long, arborent une apparence veloutée due à la présence de spores à leur surface. Loin d’être statique, Ceratiomyxa fruticulosa suit un cycle de vie semblable aux autres myxomycètes. Tout commence sous forme de spores microscopiques dispersées dans l’air. Lorsqu’elles atterrissent sur un substrat favorable, généralement du bois mort humide, elles germent et se transforment en cellules amiboïdes flagellées dotées d’une capacité de mouvement étonnante puis fusionnent pour former un plasmodium, une masse visqueuse multinucléée. Le plasmodium se développe en rampant sur le bois, engloutissant les bactéries et les champignons qui lui servent de nourriture. Au bout d’un certain temps, le plasmodium se transforme en structures reproductrices appelées sporanges. Ces sporanges libèrent à leur tour de nouvelles spores, perpétuant ainsi le cycle de vie de cet organisme étonnant. En décomposant le bois mort, il contribue au recyclage des nutriments dans le sol. J’imagine que le temps extrêmement pluvieux de cette année favorise son apparition nettement plus remarquée actuellement que d’habitude. Date: 2021-01-16 18:40:24
Caption: In 2004 I was cultivating Reishi in Chile, studying from the only books available to me. I saved up, packed the essential, & took off to take @paulstamets course on cultivating gourmet and medicinal mushrooms. He was the author of those books, and the course was taught by him at @fungiperfecti in the PNW. It was incredible! Paul (who was still heavily stammering, btw @fantasticfungi) taught with passion and intense knowledge. This is where I first met somebody who loved fungi as much as I did. A brother. It truly was an awakening for me to understand that it was ok to be mushroom mad like Paul. I learnt to cultivate lion's mane (in the photo), shiitake, oysters, and more. Was taught how to make plug spawn, grain spawn, liquid spawn. I will never forget this transformational trip during my self-learning path in mycology. If a young woman from Chile did this in the late 90's/early 2000's, you all can do it now! Shout out to my awesome classmates @bigsilly49 @postcodeman @dameinpack @traddcotter #dontstop #thinkfungi #fungiaretheforce #mushrooms #thefutureisfungi #hongos #mycelium #micelio #rotnmould #rotnmold

Caption: Peek-a-BLUE! For #Wee#Wed today, here are some Mycena interrupta, common name Pixie’s Parasol, which was very high on my list of fungi to find and photograph during my trip to Australia and New Zealand, and I was happy to see many!  I was told they are a deeper blue in Australia, but these blue beauties were found in New Zealand.  Aren’t they gorgeous!!!! The caps are stunning, and so are the gills and base of the mushroom  The second photo shows the gills, and also some of the baby blues, so precious.  What I love most about these, though, is the blue basal disc, which you can see in the closeup in the third figure.  So BLUE!

Caption: Peek-a-BLUE! For #Wee#Wed today, here are some Mycena interrupta, common name Pixie’s Parasol, which was very high on my list of fungi to find and photograph during my trip to Australia and New Zealand, and I was happy to see many!  I was told they are a deeper blue in Australia, but these blue beauties were found in New Zealand.  Aren’t they gorgeous!!!! The caps are stunning, and so are the gills and base of the mushroom  The second photo shows the gills, and also some of the baby blues, so precious.  What I love most about these, though, is the blue basal disc, which you can see in the closeup in the third figure.  So BLUE!

Date: 2023-10-22 12:40:07
Caption: Cientistas da Universidade Estadual do Ceará (Uece) criaram um fungicida natural capaz de proteger mais de 500 espécies de plantas, como cajueiro, coqueiro e pé de acerola, contra doenças como a podridão seca (causada pelo Lasiodiplodia theobromae). A descoberta recebeu carta-patente do Instituto Nacional da Propriedade Industrial (INPI). Os próximos passos dos pesquisadores serão para comercializar o produto e para realizar outros testes na avaliação do uso farmacológico da substância. As informações foram divulgadas pela comunicação da Universidade. O fungicida pode proteger plantações inteiras, com baixo custo e de forma natural, o que pode beneficiar muitos que dependem da agricultura familiar para o sustento. Além disso, há possibilidade de uso como medicamento para humanos conforme o estudo avance. Veja mais detalhes em nosso site, acessando o link que está na bio. (Foto: Uece/Reprodução) #fungicida #ciencia #Ceará #DiáriodoNordeste

Caption: Fomitopsis betulina EN This species is a saprotroph or parasite specific to Betula spp. It can be found on logs, dead trees, but sometimes in live trees too, although it possibly only infects already decaying, trees. Like other brown rot fungi it degrades the carbohydrate fraction of lignocellulose but, in contrast to white rot fungi, leaves lignin in the form of cubical brown fragments. In Portugal I have only found them growing in high altitude in mountainous areas. PT Esta espécie é um saprófito ou parasita específico de espécies do género Betula. Pode observar-se em troncos e ramos, árvores mortas, mas por vezes também em espécimes vivos, provavelmente aproveitando árvores já em mau estado fitossanitário em que a infeção é mais fácil de propagar. Como outros fungos de podridão castanha degrada a parte dos hidratos de carbono(celulose) da lignocelulose, deixando a lignina na forma de fragmentos cúbicos castanhos, em contraste com os fungos de podridão branca que degradam na forma oposta. Em Portugal só encontrei esta espécie em habitats de altitude em serras. Serra da Arada 05/2024 #fomitopsisbetulina #birchpolypore #fomitopsis #fomitopsidaceae #polyporales #polyporaceae #betula #betulapubescens #betulaceltiberica #agaricomycetes #basidiomycota #polypore #fungi #fungus #fungos #fungiphotography #fungiidentification #mushroomidentification #mushroom #mushrooms #mushroomhunting #mushroomphotography #mycophotography #mycology #micologia #cogumelos #cogumelo #wildlifephotography #wildlifephotography

Caption: Here are various stages of growth of Mycena manipularis (syn.=Filoboletus/Favolaschia manipularis) aka “Luminous Porecaps”. While these are bioluminescent - I show what they look like in daylight. Note: the second image has a different species in the mix, as Luminous Porecaps (as the name suggests-have pores, not gills). It’s interesting to see how some start out with a dark tan cap and then fade and lighten to a milky, translucent white as they age.

Caption: It’s always nice that fall gives us one more boom of mushrooms out east before winter sets in and life halts for a few months. It seems like the fall mushroom season here is mostly saprophytic species like this Mycena as well as Laetiporus, Grifola, Pleurotus, and others. Caption: This structure caught my attention as it harmonizes with nature, so I stopped to take a picture of it. I originally thought this was a coffee shop in the middle of a mountain road, away from houses but right in front of a temple. It’s just naturally beautiful in every angle. Later, I found out that it was a wood-ear beverage and sausage shop. The owners were so hospitable and kind to show us their fruiting room. They cultivate the mushroom by themselves and process it into a beverage.  I like wood-ear beverages because they are healthy. Also, it contains substances which are good for our overall health. So I bought three bottles. Besides the beverage, I bought the pink mushroom, which tasted so good when cooked with ginger and seasoned with soy sauce.  #miaoli #miaolitravel #miaolifood #woodearmushrooms #woodear #fungicultura #fungiculture #taiwantravels #taiwanmountain #mountainview #natureshots

Date: 2023-12-26 08:09:47
Caption: "Magic Mushroom Cultivation” by Steven Pollock M.D. (1977) is one of the legendary texts in the cultivation of "magic mushrooms". Many popular books were published in the US during the 70’s about the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., but this one stands out as one of the better known, particularly because in time Pollock was (incorrectly) associated with the cubensis strain "P envy". Pollock is also well known for finding and cultivating P. tampanensis, aka "Philosophers Stones". Psilocybe cubensis is one of the most cultivated mushrooms, and as a consequence of extensive collection, cultivation, breeding, and marketing ploys by various spore print sellers numerous “strains” now exist. Unfortunately, much of the history of many of the older strains has been lost, or exist within obfuscated narratives from a variety of websites, with the person/s responsible having disappeared into history. Cailleux and Heim were the first to grow cultures of P. cubensis (as Stropharia cubensis), publishing their methods in 1957. During the late 1960’s and early 1970’s, those with access to scientific literature adapted laboratory techniques for the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., notably R.E. Brown and associates who published “The Psychedelic Guide to the Preparation of the Eucharist in a Few of Its Many Guises” which was the first countercultural text to mention the cultivation of P. cubensis. Other books include “Growing Wild Mushrooms” by Harris (1976), “Psilocybin: Magic Mushroom Grower's Guide” by Oss & Oeric (1976), “How to Identify and Grow Psilocybin Mushrooms” by Gutierrez & Stevens (1977), “Teonanácatl : hallucinogenic mushrooms of North America” by Ott & Bigwood (1978), and “The mushroom Cultivator” by Stamets and Chilton(1983) #guerrillamycology #🍄 #thinkfungi #fungi #funghi #fungus #hongos #mushrooms #mycology #mycophile #mycophilia #fungiculture  #fungifanatic #mycelium #myceliumrunning #ethnomycology #radicalmycology #hallucinogenicfungi #hallucinogenic #entheogens #rogerheim #pollock #stevenpollock #magicmushroomcultivation #psilocybe #psilocybecubensis #psychedelicliterautre #penvy #philosophersstones #mushroomcultivation

Date: 2024-06-04 20:45:21
Caption: Este hongo, del género Clavaria, observado en la Quebrada de los Cuervos (Treinta y Tres) por m_coronel94, ¡es nuestra Observación del Mes en NaturalistaUY! - Los hongos pertenecen al Reino Fungi y son unos de los seres vivos más diversos de nuestro planeta. Algunos de ellos, como esta Clavaria, se alimentan de la hojarasca y materia orgánica que descomponen en los bosques. Por eso decimos que juegan un rol muy importante en el ciclado de nutrientes de los ecosistemas. Este grupo de hongos está formado por dos partes: el micelio, que crece en el sustrato, y el cuerpo fructífero, que crece en época reproductiva y normalmente podemos observar a simple vista. En el grupo de las Clavaria en particular, su forma recuerda a los corales, y por ello les llamamos “hongos coraloides”. Si bien los hongos crecen durante todo el año, en nuestro país es en otoño cuando encuentran mejores condiciones de humedad y temperatura para fructificar en mayor cantidad. Aún sabemos muy poco de este Reino. De hecho, menos del 20% de las observaciones de hongos logran ser identificadas a nivel de especie en NaturalistaUY. Para seguir construyendo conocimiento sobre nuestra biodiversidad, ¡sumate vos también a registrar tu entorno! Y si conocés de hongos, ¡ayúdanos con tus identificaciones! - Más detalles en https://www.naturalista.uy/observations/213830990 #reinofungi #coralfungi #Clavariaceae #mushroomidentification #mushroomobserver #observaciondelmesnaturalistauy

Caption: #Repost @marin_mushrooms: For #WeeWednesday today, here are some teensy tiny mushrooms, Mycena adscendens, that I found in a small redwood forest in Golden Gate Park some time ago.  The common name for these is Frosty bonnet, and it is easy to see why.  Look at those beautiful sugar-like crystals on the cap!   The larger of these two mushrooms is only about one millimeter tall --  that's quite a bit less than the thickness of a US dime!  The second photo shows these two tiny ones with a slightly more grown up specimen, where you can see the lovely gills.  The last photo is a phone photo (and a very bad one, sorry) showing these mushrooms next to the tip of a ballpoint pen so you can see how really tiny they are. Caption: 🍄Hongo Sombrero Violeta o Cortinarius Magellanicus Se encuentra en el sur de #Chile y #Argentina, y fructifica entre enero y mayo. Es una especie micorrizógena, que crece cerca de árboles principalmente del género Nothofagus. Como se puede ver en la fotografía su color es violáceo con tintes púrpuras. Este hongo presenta un sombrero de 1 a 8 cm de diámetro. Tanto el sombrero como el estipe están cubiertos de una capa mucilaginosa. La esporada es de color pardo. Caption: ℹ️ Dünnsporiges Kranzbecherchen (Vibrissea flavorirens) Vibrissea flavorirens ist ein Bewohner sauberer Bäche, Quellsümpfe usw. Es besiedelt, oft sehr zahlreich, entrindete, harte Laubholzäste, die ständig von fließendem Wasser umspült werden. Die Apothecien werden ca 2-3mm groß, sind kurz gestielt und haben einen charakteristischen, zahnradähnlich gekerbten Rand. Die dünnen Fäden, die auf dem letzten Bild im Hintergrund herumfliegen, sind die, mit bis 250μm Länge, riesigen Sporen. 🗓️ 26.05.2024 🍴 ungenießbar 🚩 Rote Liste (DE): Vorwarnliste #vibrisseaflavovirens #dünnsporigeskranzbecherchen #pilze #fungi #mushrooms #mycology #nature #pilzfotografie #mushroomphotography #pilzesammeln #pilzesuchen #mushroomhunting #mushroomsofınstagram #fungiofinstagram #fungilove #fantasticfungi #fungifreaks #makrofotografie #macrophotography #forestfinds #darmstadt #spessart #rotelistepilze

Caption: ℹ️ Dünnsporiges Kranzbecherchen (Vibrissea flavorirens) Vibrissea flavorirens ist ein Bewohner sauberer Bäche, Quellsümpfe usw. Es besiedelt, oft sehr zahlreich, entrindete, harte Laubholzäste, die ständig von fließendem Wasser umspült werden. Die Apothecien werden ca 2-3mm groß, sind kurz gestielt und haben einen charakteristischen, zahnradähnlich gekerbten Rand. Die dünnen Fäden, die auf dem letzten Bild im Hintergrund herumfliegen, sind die, mit bis 250μm Länge, riesigen Sporen. 🗓️ 26.05.2024 🍴 ungenießbar 🚩 Rote Liste (DE): Vorwarnliste #vibrisseaflavovirens #dünnsporigeskranzbecherchen #pilze #fungi #mushrooms #mycology #nature #pilzfotografie #mushroomphotography #pilzesammeln #pilzesuchen #mushroomhunting #mushroomsofınstagram #fungiofinstagram #fungilove #fantasticfungi #fungifreaks #makrofotografie #macrophotography #forestfinds #darmstadt #spessart #rotelistepilze

Caption: You're so golden! 💛 The Golden-scruffy Collybia (Cyptotrama asprata) is found all around the world. In Australia it's primarily found along the east coast. With a cushion-shaped mushroom cap that grows up to 2.7 centimetres in diameter, it's covered in bright yellow and orange protrusions that lose their vibrancy as the mushroom ages. It's a saprobic fungus, so it processes dead and decaying wood from deciduous and coniferous trees. 🌲 📸 | Byteme via @inaturalistorg / Atlas of Living Australia *CSIRO does not endorse the consumption of any fungus referenced in #FungiFriday* #GoldenHour #OohSpiky #AtlasofLivingAustralia #WeLoveScience #CSIRO

Date: 2022-02-06 08:49:48
Caption: Amanita muscaria, Fly Agaric, Amanitaceae. An introduced species to Australia, it is mycorrhizal with northern hemisphere conifers and hardwoods. Autumn and winter is when A. muscaria dominates the pine forests of Australia, though after the amount of rainfall we have had this summer, it’s not unusual to have them popping up now, in the same way Lactarius deliciosus (saffron milk cap) has been plentiful this summer. I was puzzled when I found this, as it was in the middle of a Eucalyptus forest, though after looking around I found two Pinus radiata growing a little way away. Known around the world for a variety of reasons, it has been portrayed in folklore, prepared in the kitchen for food, as medicine, and as a hallucinogen (it contains ibotenic acid, a neurotoxin which converts to muscimol, a psychoactive compound, once digested). Amanita muscaria poses a serious threat to the biodiversity of native fungi in the Myrtle Beech forests of Victoria and Tasmania, where it has formed Mycohrriza with Nothofagus cunninghamii.

Caption: Fomitopsis betulina EN This species is a saprotroph or parasite specific to Betula spp. It can be found on logs, dead trees, but sometimes in live trees too, although it possibly only infects already decaying, trees. Like other brown rot fungi it degrades the carbohydrate fraction of lignocellulose but, in contrast to white rot fungi, leaves lignin in the form of cubical brown fragments. In Portugal I have only found them growing in high altitude in mountainous areas. PT Esta espécie é um saprófito ou parasita específico de espécies do género Betula. Pode observar-se em troncos e ramos, árvores mortas, mas por vezes também em espécimes vivos, provavelmente aproveitando árvores já em mau estado fitossanitário em que a infeção é mais fácil de propagar. Como outros fungos de podridão castanha degrada a parte dos hidratos de carbono(celulose) da lignocelulose, deixando a lignina na forma de fragmentos cúbicos castanhos, em contraste com os fungos de podridão branca que degradam na forma oposta. Em Portugal só encontrei esta espécie em habitats de altitude em serras. Date: 2022-02-20 16:14:00
Caption: Happy #SlimeMoldSunday to Myxomycete lovers new and old! These amazing myxo fruiting bodies are Diachea leucopodia, one of my favorites because of their beautiful iridescence.  As with many slime molds, this species changes colors several times during its brief life cycle.  When they first arise from the white plasmodium, the fruiting bodies are white.  They then turn almost black, and as they mature and dry the peridium (outer covering of the spore-containing body) turns into these strikingly beautiful iridescent blue, purple, and brown colors on a white stout stalk.  Although the individual fruiting bodies are tiny, only 1-2mm tall, they can be easy to spot because they grow in dense and large clusters on leaves, grasses, and live and decaying plant material.  To see how tiny they are, see the second photo, which shows a few fruiting bodies on a twig with the tip of a fine point pen for scale. A little technical info for those of you who might be interested.  To photograph such tiny myxos with sharp detail, I use an extreme macro lens.  With such high magnifications, the depth of field (portion of the subject that is in sharp focus) is less than 0.05mm. To get a photo of the entire fruiting body in focus, I use a technique called focus stacking. My camera is mounted on a finely tuned rail, and the camera is moved in minuscule increments between each photo, so that the focal point changes with each photo.   For this photo, I took 138 individual images, which were then “stacked” with specialized computer software that combines the most in-focus portions of each of the individual images into a composite image that shows everything in focus from front to back.

Date: 2022-10-03 11:47:28
Caption: Dendrocollybia racemosa - Branched shanklet Not my find but a collaborative effort to collect and record this rare species. I’m thrilled to get the opportunity to witness this one. The location has been recorded, and pending permissions, a sample will be making its way to Kew Gardens to be included in their genome sequencing projects and the national collection. Found by: Nicky Freeman Collected & record by: Iona Fraser @ashdownforage The species is characterised by its unusual stem, which is covered with short lateral branches. The branches often produce spherical slimeheads of translucent conidiophores  on their swollen tips. The conidiophores produce conidia (asexual spores) by mitosis. Because the fungus can rely on either sexual or asexual modes of reproduction, fruit bodies sometimes have reduced or even missing caps. The unusual stems originate from black pea-sized structures called sclerotia. The anamorphic form of the fungus, known as Tilachlidiopsis racemosa, is missing the sexual stage of its life cycle. It can reproduce at relatively low temperatures, an adaptation believed to improve its ability to grow quickly and fruit on decomposing mushrooms. (Info via Wikimili) #allthingsfungi

Caption: Here are various stages of growth of Mycena manipularis (syn.=Filoboletus/Favolaschia manipularis) aka “Luminous Porecaps”. It’s interesting to see how some start out with a dark tan cap and then fade and lighten to a milky, translucent white as they age.

Caption: Growing your own shiitake mushrooms on logs in your garden is surprisingly easy. You inoculate some wood, wait a year or two (yes, it does require a bit of patience) and then, one rainy day, you get a harvest of homegrown shiitakes! And then more and more from those same logs each year, for about the next five years.⁠ ⁠ Once you get into the swing of it, you can inoculate a few additional logs each autumn - ensuring a never-ending harvest and thus plenty of big warming bowls of mushroom ramen and stir-fried shiitake and everything delicious and wonderful.⁠ ⁠ So, want to know exactly what we mean by 'inoculate logs'?⁠ ⁠ At the link in our bio, we have a free Getting Started With Mushroom Cultivation guide, which includes a section on how to grow shiitake on logs. It'll help get your head around the basics, including:⁠ 🪵 What supplies you need.⁠ 🪵 How to prepare your substrate.⁠ 🪵 Inoculation and incubation.⁠ 🪵 And a little trick we learned to help bring on fruiting.⁠ ⁠ Alrighty, lovely - go download your guide, have a read and then let us know if you have any questions? We're always here to help. Caption: No son plantas, tampoco animales, entonces... ¿Qué son? 🤔🍄 Las setas o callampas que solemos ver en otoño, de diversas formas, tamaños y colores son la parte exterior de algunos hongos que viven bajo tierra o dentro de la materia orgánica en descomposición 🦠🍄 Los hongos son uno de los cinco reinos en que se agrupan a los seres vivos y, por lo tanto, no se consideran ni plantas, ni animales 🍄 No son vegetales, pues no realizan fotosíntesis. Tampoco son animales, pues no ingieren su alimento, lo absorben y sus células tienen pared celular 🧬🍄 Debido a estas razones estos organismos están situados en su propio reino biológico llamado Fungi 🍄 Está es solo una de las muchas curiosidades que podemos aprender sobre estos importantes y lindos seres vivos 🥹🍄 Aprovecho que es otoño temporada donde los vemos por todas partes, así iré enseñando fotitos y videos de las variedades que encontré por estos lados, y por supuesto otras curiosidades sobre ellos 🍄🍄 Recuerda darle amor a este post 💚 #hongo #otoño #hongos #fungi #vidafungi #fungilove #naturaleza #plantas #lamacetitachile #fungichile #valdivia #amanita #amanitas

Date: 2022-02-06 08:49:48
Caption: Amanita muscaria, Fly Agaric, Amanitaceae. An introduced species to Australia, it is mycorrhizal with northern hemisphere conifers and hardwoods. Autumn and winter is when A. muscaria dominates the pine forests of Australia, though after the amount of rainfall we have had this summer, it’s not unusual to have them popping up now, in the same way Lactarius deliciosus (saffron milk cap) has been plentiful this summer. I was puzzled when I found this, as it was in the middle of a Eucalyptus forest, though after looking around I found two Pinus radiata growing a little way away. Known around the world for a variety of reasons, it has been portrayed in folklore, prepared in the kitchen for food, as medicine, and as a hallucinogen (it contains ibotenic acid, a neurotoxin which converts to muscimol, a psychoactive compound, once digested). Amanita muscaria poses a serious threat to the biodiversity of native fungi in the Myrtle Beech forests of Victoria and Tasmania, where it has formed Mycohrriza with Nothofagus cunninghamii.

Date: 2023-12-26 08:09:47
Caption: "Magic Mushroom Cultivation” by Steven Pollock M.D. (1977) is one of the legendary texts in the cultivation of "magic mushrooms". Many popular books were published in the US during the 70’s about the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., but this one stands out as one of the better known, particularly because in time Pollock was (incorrectly) associated with the cubensis strain "P envy". Pollock is also well known for finding and cultivating P. tampanensis, aka "Philosophers Stones". Psilocybe cubensis is one of the most cultivated mushrooms, and as a consequence of extensive collection, cultivation, breeding, and marketing ploys by various spore print sellers numerous “strains” now exist. Unfortunately, much of the history of many of the older strains has been lost, or exist within obfuscated narratives from a variety of websites, with the person/s responsible having disappeared into history. Cailleux and Heim were the first to grow cultures of P. cubensis (as Stropharia cubensis), publishing their methods in 1957. During the late 1960’s and early 1970’s, those with access to scientific literature adapted laboratory techniques for the cultivation of Psilocybe spp., notably R.E. Brown and associates who published “The Psychedelic Guide to the Preparation of the Eucharist in a Few of Its Many Guises” which was the first countercultural text to mention the cultivation of P. cubensis. Other books include “Growing Wild Mushrooms” by Harris (1976), “Psilocybin: Magic Mushroom Grower's Guide” by Oss & Oeric (1976), “How to Identify and Grow Psilocybin Mushrooms” by Gutierrez & Stevens (1977), “Teonanácatl : hallucinogenic mushrooms of North America” by Ott & Bigwood (1978), and “The mushroom Cultivator” by Stamets and Chilton(1983) #guerrillamycology #🍄 #thinkfungi #fungi #funghi #fungus #hongos #mushrooms #mycology #mycophile #mycophilia #fungiculture  #fungifanatic #mycelium #myceliumrunning #ethnomycology #radicalmycology #hallucinogenicfungi #hallucinogenic #entheogens #rogerheim #pollock #stevenpollock #magicmushroomcultivation #psilocybe #psilocybecubensis #psychedelicliterautre #penvy #philosophersstones #mushroomcultivation

Caption: 🆔Inosperma erubescens (Inocybe erubescens) 👉🏽Deadly Fibrecap, brick-red tear mushroom 👉🏽Ziegelroter Risspilz 👉🏽变红丝盖伞 (reddening silk top umbrella) 🌟 The brick-red splitting mushroom (Inocybe erubescens) can be found on forest paths, in parks, or in deciduous forests, especially under beech or linden trees on calcareous, nutrient-rich soils. 🌳🍃 The fruit bodies of this mushroom appear from spring/early summer until late autumn. 🌸🍂 🌟 磚紅裂褶菇（Inocybe erubescens）可以在林間小徑、公園或闊葉林中找到，特別是在含鈣、富營養的土壤中的山毛櫸或菩提樹下。🌳🍃 這種蘑菇的子實體從春季/初夏到晚秋出現。🌸🍂 ⚠️ **WARNING:** Inocybe erubescens contains a potentially fatal dose of the toxin muscarine. ⚠️😱 However, its deadly toxicity depends on the amount consumed; a small piece might not cause severe illness, but eating an entire mushroom can be fatal. 🍄☠️ ⚠️ **警告：** 磚紅裂褶菇含有致命劑量的毒素——毒蕈鹼。⚠️😱 然而，其致命毒性取決於攝入量；少量可能不會引起嚴重疾病，但食用整個蘑菇可能致命。🍄☠️ 📚 All mushroom guidebooks and mushroom hunters advise against consuming any members of the Inocybaceae family! ❌🚫 📚 所有的蘑菇指南書和蘑菇獵人都建議不要食用任何Inocybaceae科的成員！❌🚫 Today, when I discovered these Inocybe mushrooms in the village next to some linden trees, I had to lie down on the ground to take pictures and examine them carefully. 📸👀 This was when a car stopped right behind me, and a man got out to ask if everything was okay. 🚗💨 I felt a bit awkward but reassured him that I was fine. 😅 It was heartening to see that people care if someone is spread out on the ground, regardless of the reason. ❤️🙏 今天，當我在村子裡的一些菩提樹旁發現這些裂褶菇時，我不得不躺在地上拍照並仔細檢查它們。📸👀 就在這時，一輛車停在我身後，一位男士下車問我是否一切正常。🚗💨 我感到有點尷尬，但我向他保證我沒事。😅 看到人們關心無論何種原因躺在地上的人，這讓我感到很暖心。❤️🙏 #InocybeErubescens 🍄🌿🕵️‍♂️ I tried some microscopy on this one. 🔬🧬 Image one shows cheilocystidia, and in between the two big cheilocystidia is a basidium with two sterigmata (they look like tiny antennas). 🧫🔍 The second microscopy image shows spores, which are oval to almond-shaped. I used Melzer's reagent to stain the sample. 🧪📸 Oh my, microscopy terminology is really hard! Definitely need to catch up. 😅 In case you know any of the terms in Chinese, please feel free to comment. Cheilozystidia 緣擔孢子囊 Basidia 擔子 Sterigmata 擔梗

Caption: Happy full moon #mushroomlovers 🌑🌘🌗🌖🌕🌔🌓🌒🌑 #Repost from @symbiiotica 🍄 How do lunar cycles influence the cycles of fungi? Considering the fact that lunar gravity influences every being on this planet, especially water bodies and those with water-based bodies (most of life), and considering the fact that most mushrooms are > 90% water… it’s almost certain that the moons influences plays SOME role in fungal fruitings, behaviors and expressions. Many Indigenous cultures that have deeply rooted ethnomycological history, especially those of the northern hemisphere in Scandinavia and Siberia, claim that fruitings of ground-dwelling, fleshy macrofungi occur in greater abundance on the full moon. Since the moons gravity pulls the terrestrial tides (ground water) further up to the surface of the soil on full moons and even more so on new moons, it would make sense that lunar events have a direct effect on fruiting of certain species. But for now the exact knowing of these influences stays happily shrouded in mystery. What the moons exact role is in fungal cycles, we just don’t really know. And maybe we’ll never know. And that’s okay. ~ Here is a rendition of the basic life cycle of a basidiomycete mushroom cycling with the lunar phases. From my perspective, I’ve matched the different energetic expressions of the mushroom life cycle with the associated energetic expressions of the lunar cycle. From full; the biggest, boldest, brightest expression of the mature, sporulating fruiting body, to new; the deep, dark inquisitive phase of underground, rhizospheric mycelial navigation, and back again. In the center is the Elder Futhark Norse Rune, Inguz. The Elder Futhark runic alphabet is said to be the most ancient form of the many Indigenous writing systems from my Scandinavian ancestral lineages(s). Inguz or “the God, Ing” is the rune of fertility and new beginnings, marking a new phase of life. Also interpreted as a seed, the birthing of a new idea or life form. The shape also represents a doorway, the portal to the astral planes.

Caption: The Future is Fungal 🍄 Fungi fashion? Fungi furniture? Fungi foundations? 🧐 Not only is this attractive alliteration, but it just might be the future of fungi. With its ability to grow rapidly, fit any form, and carry a carbon-neutral footprint, mycelium makes the perfect building material for companies eyeing a more sustainable future. 💫 Mycelium leather has already caught the eyes of industry giants like Adidas, Lululemon, and Stella McCartney. Chairs, canoes, and entire structures have been constructed from fungi. It’s also being used as a replacement for Styrofoam in packaging – eliminating one of the worst environmental pollutants we have. 🙌 Fungi have served as the building blocks for life on Earth for millennia and now we are discovering its immense potential to integrate them to design for our human habitats. The best part is that this is a mutually beneficial relationship for both modern civilization and the natural world. Because mycelium grows agricultural waste the inputs are abundant and dirt cheap, making it an extremely economically viable process. This is only the beginning of the ‘shroom-boom’! 💥 Check out our friends at @soma.eco to discover the latest in mycelial technology! Date: 2022-11-09 20:43:42
Caption: Amanita muscaria🍄 es una especie cosmopolita que crece en el sur de Chile🇨🇱, principalmente en la zona de Valdivia y sus alrededores, sin embargo se puede encontrar en casi todas las zonas donde existen predios forestales plantados con pino🌲 radiata. El único uso documentado para Amanita muscaria corresponde a la utilización en contexto chamanico. Aunque Amanita muscaria es un hongo cosmopolita solo ha sido utilizado en algunas culturas indígenas de Estados Unidos🇺🇸, Rusia 🇷🇺y Mesoamérica. Actualmente, Amanita muscaria es consumido a baja escala como un alucinógeno 😵‍💫de uso recreativo, en donde no existe un guía o Chaman. Por lo cual resulta en la mayoría de las ocasiones un consumo irresponsable y bastante peligroso. No existe ningún proceso seguro que elimine todas las toxinas en A. muscaria, sin embargo, si se va a consumir se recomienda secarla al sol, pues este proceso disminuye la toxicidad de la muscarina o toxina mata moscas. El secado al sol🌞 también ayuda en la descarboxilación parcial del ácido iboténico, el cual se transforma en muscimol, sustancia que es aproximadamente 10 veces más alucinógeno. La acción farmacológica del muscimol es diferente de la psilocibina (Psilocibes spp. “Cucumelo”), ya que actúa como agonista del receptor GABAa. Los riesgos pueden disminuir más si se consume solo la película roja externa del sombrero y la capa que yace inmediatamente por debajo, en el hongo seco. 🛑NUNCA SE DEBE CONSUMIR FRESCO y siempre acompañado de un cuidador o alguna persona que no consuma. 👉Ante todas las recomendaciones pertinentes, siempre es mejor no consumir Amanita muscaria para su uso recreativo. 🛩️Comparte si te gustó Créditos @mushroom_and_us @vicentevaldesguzmanphotography #amanita #amanitamuscaria #setas #hongos #fungi #reinofungi #fungilover #picfee #fotoverweij #photographersassociates #ig_discover_holland #igholland #dutch_connextion #catch_holland #dutchphotoacademy #thiswaymoments #heelnederland_fotografeert #holland_photolovers #nb_nature_brilliance #vroegevogels_bnnvara

Caption: #Repost @marin_mushrooms: For #WeeWednesday today, here are some teensy tiny mushrooms, Mycena adscendens, that I found in a small redwood forest in Golden Gate Park some time ago.  The common name for these is Frosty bonnet, and it is easy to see why.  Look at those beautiful sugar-like crystals on the cap!   The larger of these two mushrooms is only about one millimeter tall --  that's quite a bit less than the thickness of a US dime!  The second photo shows these two tiny ones with a slightly more grown up specimen, where you can see the lovely gills.  The last photo is a phone photo (and a very bad one, sorry) showing these mushrooms next to the tip of a ballpoint pen so you can see how really tiny they are. Caption: #Repost @marin_mushrooms: For #WeeWednesday today, here are some teensy tiny mushrooms, Mycena adscendens, that I found in a small redwood forest in Golden Gate Park some time ago.  The common name for these is Frosty bonnet, and it is easy to see why.  Look at those beautiful sugar-like crystals on the cap!   The larger of these two mushrooms is only about one millimeter tall --  that's quite a bit less than the thickness of a US dime!  The second photo shows these two tiny ones with a slightly more grown up specimen, where you can see the lovely gills.  The last photo is a phone photo (and a very bad one, sorry) showing these mushrooms next to the tip of a ballpoint pen so you can see how really tiny they are. Date: 2024-05-31 21:30:36
Caption: ✨𝗜𝗻 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗺𝘆𝘅’✨ Imaginez un organisme à la croisée des règnes animal et végétal, qui se développe comme une plante mais se déplace comme un animal. C’est 𝗖𝗲𝗿𝗮𝘁𝗶𝗼𝗺𝘆𝘅𝗮 𝗳𝗿𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗰𝘂𝗹𝗼𝘀𝗮, un myxomycète. Il se présente sous une forme étonnante, rappelant un corail miniature ou de minuscules stalactites. Ses ramifications blanches se développent sur les bois morts, formant des structures délicates et complexes. Ces ramifications, mesurant jusqu’à 4 millimètres de long, arborent une apparence veloutée due à la présence de spores à leur surface. Loin d’être statique, Ceratiomyxa fruticulosa suit un cycle de vie semblable aux autres myxomycètes. Tout commence sous forme de spores microscopiques dispersées dans l’air. Lorsqu’elles atterrissent sur un substrat favorable, généralement du bois mort humide, elles germent et se transforment en cellules amiboïdes flagellées dotées d’une capacité de mouvement étonnante puis fusionnent pour former un plasmodium, une masse visqueuse multinucléée. Le plasmodium se développe en rampant sur le bois, engloutissant les bactéries et les champignons qui lui servent de nourriture. Au bout d’un certain temps, le plasmodium se transforme en structures reproductrices appelées sporanges. Ces sporanges libèrent à leur tour de nouvelles spores, perpétuant ainsi le cycle de vie de cet organisme étonnant. En décomposant le bois mort, il contribue au recyclage des nutriments dans le sol. J’imagine que le temps extrêmement pluvieux de cette année favorise son apparition nettement plus remarquée actuellement que d’habitude. Caption: Growing a new fungus is always interesting. This is Cordyceps militaris #cordycepsmilitaris a fungi that until recently was not allowed to be grown here in Australia.
